			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">You should be able to solo this zone easily at 44. The initial pull will net you two mobs, but after that it's relatively easy to pull singles. Keep in mind that a lot of CoM is undead, so a lot of things will see through invis. Scouting with Eye of Zomm is a very good thing. 
<br />

<br />
Once you zone in and go down the hall a little bit, go ahead and call your pet and buff him up. It's up to you whether you want to really buff the heck out of him by using pet toys (Girdle of Magi-Kot, Muzzle of Mardu, etc) or just chain cast. Either way be prepared to get two mobs on your first pull. The good thing is, as long as you stay back and don't nuke too much, they'll ignore you and beat the crap out of your pet. The second good thing is they don't hit terribly hard compared to some of the other mobs at this level in Velious and Luclin. If you're going to buff and heal, I would suggest keeping two heal spells loaded for this first round so you can chain heal.
<br />

<br />
Call your eye, and scout ahead so you can see exactly where the first two mobs are, since they're behind a corner when you first zone in. Once you have one targeted you can try to pull one with your debuff spell to see if you can get just one (although, honestly I've never been able to single pull them) or you can simply send in the pet and let both mobs get good agro. A damage shield on the pet will help with this if you plan to go the heal route.
<br />

<br />
Once you finish off those two mobs, carefully cross the bridge and open the gate from as far away as possible, so you don't agro the mobs just inside the gate. Those mobs can usually be single pulled. Once you've cleared those, turn to your left. There will be a small grassy area to your immediate right and one mob at the end of a hallway in front of you. Once you kill him, you can set up your camp where he spawns and pull the rest of the courtyard in relative peace. He's not a quick respawn, but I can't remember the exact timing on it, since I haven't been there in a while. Try to time it the first cycle so you'll know for the rest of your stay. And during that first round, try not to get low on mana, in case he pops on you unexpectedly.
<br />

<br />
CoM is considered an outdoor zone, so if you have a mount, you'll be able to use it here, which is nice. Once the courtyard mobs start turning light blue, the hallway behind where you're set up leads to the "Stable" area. You can then start camping that area. Be careful though. Since the revamp there are a number of named mobs that pop in the Stable area occasionally, and were light blue and dark blue to my level 61 druid. As you're facing the stable area, the right side is easier to pull than the left side. You'll get multiples much easier pulling the left side. I would usually pull the right side and most of the time get single pulls and clean out the right side before stopping to med up again.
<br />

<br />
Once you hit 50 you'll be plowing through those mobs in no time flat. But at that point I would suggest heading over to Nurga to try your luck there. My notes, and those of others on the delights of Nurga are listed in the 50-55 and 55-60 forums.<br />_________________<br />Get your mind out of the gutter. While you're down there, get mine too.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
